Results.ItemName: CAMUSSO STERLING SILVER FLATWARE DESERT FORK-1

LotInfo.LotDescript: CAMUSSO STERLING SILVER FLATWARE Embassy pattern.
May need to be professionally restored repaired.
Approximately 24 pieces that include Desert Fork.
Halmark .925, Length is 7" and total weight of
all 24 pieces is approximately 2 lbs. Previously
used at U. S. Embassies in foreign locations.
PROPERTY REMOVAL: Due to security issues at
property location, successful bidders are
required to contact the custodian 72 hours prior
to being allowed into the facility to remove
property. Must be a U.S. citizen and have a
government issued picture ID (driver's license,
etc.). Appointments are required. No electronics
are permitted to be brought into this Government
building; therefore, successful bidders must
communicate with the custodian in advance to make
arrangements for removal. Successful BIDDERS are
cautioned that they ARE RESPONSIBLE for packing,
loading and removal of all property awarded to
them from where the property is located.

LotInfo.LotDescript: 1984 Hi'ialakai vessel, make: Tacoma Boat
Building Co., Hull ID: R-334, serial: CG001964,
model: T-AGOS-3. Include a displacement of 1,650
tons (light) and 2,285 tons (full load), gross
tons 1,914. The overall length of the ship is 224
ft with a 43 ft beam, 16 ft draft, and 20 ft
depth. PCB non-detectable, Asbestos not detected,
Lead based paint determined in 4 areas of concern
(>1.0 mg/cm(sq)). Ship's propulsion provided by
General Electric 800 hp diesel electric motors
with twin shafts. The ship was able to reach
speeds of 11 knots and cruises at 10 knots. The
overall range of the ship is 20,000 nautical
miles or approximately 35 days. The ship can
carry two work boats and a fast rescue boat.
Hotel and drive power supplied by four diesel
generators. The diesel generators have
Caterpillar prime movers with Kato Generators
currently non-operational. Vessel will require
towing. It is highly recommended that bidders
conduct ship visits. Additionally, the NOAA Ship
Hi'ialakai equipment includes multibeam sonar and
echo sounder equipment for underwater mapping
work. Additional features include a wet and dry
lab, and electronics laboratory. On deck, there
is a 46-foot telescoping boom with a designed
lifting capacity of 6,600 pounds at full
extension, an A-frame with a maximum safe working
load of 22,000 pounds, and a J-frame with a
maximum safe working load of 3,500 pounds. The
ship was designed to support up to 50 people.
Repairs needed but not limited to: Need rust
repair, electrical repair & emergency generator
repair. Additional information regarding the
vessel is attached in the below link. Repairs are
required. ****Purchaser must sign a hazardous
form. Submit statement to
charmaine.bailey@gsa.gov****. **** This is
considered to be hazardous materials and the
bidder will have to comply with all regulations
and restrictions for local, state, and federal
governments in regards to transportation and
disposal of hazardous materials. The bidder
hereby certifies that if awarded a contract under
this invitation for bids, the bidder will comply
with all applicable federal, state, and local
laws, ordinances, and regulations, with respect
to the care, handling, storage, shipment, resale,
export, or other use of the material hereby
purchased. The bidder will hold the government
harmless from any or all debts, liabilities,
judgments, costs, demands, suits, actions, or
other claims of any nature arising from or
incident to the handling, use, storage, shipment,
resale, export, or other disposition of the
hazardous items purchased.**** **** The
successful bidder of this property will be
required to complete an "End Use Certificate"
prior to removing the vessel. Document attached
and submit to charmaine.bailey@gsa.gov or fax to
Certification Approval Process can take
approximately 30 to 60 days**. Individuals
bidding on this sale must be U.S. Citizens and
must be able to provide naturalization paperwork,
passport, or approved photo identification.
****These requirements are mandated by Department
of Defense. As the Contracting Officer of this
sale, I encourage you to not make arrangements
for removal until you have received approval
status from Department of Defense****.
